Articles.Content:
For anyone who would like to use static radiators with NFE reactors, I wrote a ModuleManager patch that changes static panels from passive to active. The new heat parameters are identical to folding radiators. I also decreased static radiators' cost so there is a reason to consider using them. Nertea, you're welcome to include this as an optional patch for NFE if you like.

    @PART[radPanelSm]{	@cost = 50	@heatConductivity = 0.001	%skinInternalConductionMult = 2000	@radiatorHeadroom = 0.75	@thermalMassModifier = 2.5	MODULE	{		name = ModuleActiveRadiator		maxEnergyTransfer = 500	}}@PART[radPanelLg]{	@cost = 250	@heatConductivity = 0.001	%skinInternalConductionMult = 2000	@radiatorHeadroom = 0.75	@thermalMassModifier = 2.5	MODULE	{		name = ModuleActiveRadiator		maxEnergyTransfer = 2500	}}

**Edited <time datetime="2015-07-05T06:27:52Z" title="07/05/2015 06:27  AM" data-short="9 yr">July 5, 2015</time> by Fraz86**
